<a class="platform-card" href="https://www.iheart.com/podcast/1333-a-little-throuple-tea-gay-291849404" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" height="97" loading="lazy" src="/images/iheartradio.png" width="78"/><span>iHeartRadio</span></a>
<a class="platform-card" href="https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCswzye8bcm8bByqLlW0QaFQ" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" height="269" loading="lazy" src="/images/youtube.png" width="640"/><span>YouTube</span></a>
<a class="platform-card" href="https://music.amazon.com/podcasts/2a3cfc8f-2a79-4aac-b48b-625a20f08421/3dudes1life-a-little-throuple-tea" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" height="97" loading="lazy" src="/images/amazon_music.png" width="117"/><span>Amazon Music</span></a>
<a class="platform-card" href="https://anchor.fm/s/1087008c4/podcast/rss" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank"><img alt="" decoding="async" height="512" loading="lazy" src="/images/rss.png" width="512"/><span>RSS Feed</span></a>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="section">
<div class="wrap latest-grid">
<div class="video-shell">
<iframe allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/fqCHTiXzCMA" title="A Little Throuple Tea podcast trailer"></iframe>
</div>
<div>
<div class="eyebrow">Start here</div>
<h2 class="section-title">Meet the gay throuple behind the microphones.</h2>
<p class="section-lede">William, Caleb and Daniel have spent years building a committed life together. The podcast turns that real relationship into conversations about love, conflict, family, aging, sex, finances, travel and every ridiculous detour in between.</p>
<div class="cta-row">
<a class="btn primary" href="/meet-the-throuple/">Meet William, Caleb + Daniel</a>
<a class="btn" href="/gay-throuple-podcast/">Why this podcast is different</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="section">
<div class="wrap">
<h2 class="section-title">A relationship podcast that refuses to pretend life is perfect.</h2>
<p class="section-lede">A Little Throuple Tea combines modern LGBTQ+ relationship stories with the chemistry of three longtime partners who actually share a home, finances, family, dogs, projects and a future.</p>
<div class="feature-grid">
<article class="feature-card"><small>Real relationships</small><h3>Throuple life without the fantasy edit</h3><p>Jealousy, communication, boundaries, commitment, pair dynamics and the practical work of making a three-person relationship function.</p></article>
<article class="feature-card"><small>Queer life</small><h3>LGBTQ+ culture, family and community</h3><p>Stories about identity, chosen family, getting older, public visibility and building a life that does not fit the old template.</p></article>
<article class="feature-card"><small>Pure chaos</small><h3>Travel, paranormal nonsense and terrible decisions</h3><p>Lake trips, casinos, haunted houses, neighborhood drama, pop culture and whatever absurd topic enters the studio that week.</p></article>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<section class="section">
<div class="wrap hosts-grid">
<article class="host-card"><h3>William</h3><p>Founder, author, storyteller and the host most likely to turn one small observation into a full investigation.</p></article>
<article class="host-card"><h3>Caleb</h3><p>The grounding force, dry delivery specialist and frequent unwilling participant in whatever chaos William started.</p></article>
<article class="host-card"><h3>Daniel</h3><p>The intuitive one, the plot-twist provider and the host capable of taking a conversation somewhere nobody expected.</p></article>
</div>
</section>
<section class="section" id="discover">
<div class="wrap search-cluster">
<article class="seo-copy">
<div class="eyebrow">Gay throuple podcast</div>
<h2>What is a throuple—and what does one actually look like in real life?</h2>
<p>A throuple is a romantic relationship involving three people. Some throuples are open, while William, Caleb and Daniel are committed exclusively to one another as a closed triad.</p>
<p style="margin-top:16px;"><a class="btn primary" href="/what-is-a-throuple/">Read the complete throuple explainer</a></p>
</article>
